content:
Convert Page Layouts for Case Feed Users to Case Page Layouts

As of Spring '14, creating and customizing case layouts has been made easier by replacing page layouts for Case Feed users with feed-based layouts for case pages. To convert your older page layouts:

Go to Object Management Settings for cases, then click on a layout in the Page Layouts for Case Feed Users list and choose Convert to case page layout.

The converted layout appears in the Case Page Layouts list with the prefix Converted:. Confirm that it includes the desired elements. Assign the new case page layout using the standard page layout assignment tool.

Recommended: Use this option so you can review the converted layout before deleting the original. You can also choose Convert to page layout and delete, but confirm that the layout includes the desired elements.

Delete the older version of the layout in the Page Layouts for Case Feed Users list. When you assign users to a case page layout, they'll see the new layout.

Required Editions: Available in Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.
User Permissions: Customize Application (to create and edit page layouts), Manage Users (to assign page layouts). 

Feed-based case layouts include a feed, highlights panel, detail page with related lists, and sidebar components. You can use the standard page layout assignment tool to assign feed-based case page layouts to users.
title: Converting Case Feed User Page Layouts to Case Page Layouts
